-- Ukraine’s Sovereign Debt Fell 0.5% in February, Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-03-26T14:43:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/ukraine-s-sovereign-debt-fell-0-5-in-february-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s debt, including state
guarantees, declined 0.5 percent last month as the country
repaid part of its credit with the  International Monetary Fund ,
the  Finance Ministry  said.  Debt dropped to $59.21 billion as of Feb. 29 from $59.48
billion a month earlier, the ministry said today in a  statement 
on its website.  Ukraine repaid $575 million of debt to the IMF in February.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
